  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Tide in tremolo mode (mode 0) at 0.35 Hz gives the supersaw an organic swell that velocity modulates — harder playing pushes the tremolo depth into amplitude gating. The Tide stereo phase at 60 degrees produces a kelp-field sway rather than simple pulsing: each side breathes slightly out of phase.",
